<div class="note" topic="statutoryNotes"><span class="heading centered"><strong>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</strong></span></div>
<div class="note" topic="changeOfName">
<span class="heading centered smallCaps">Change of Name</span>
<p><span link="https://liicornell.org/liifedent/broadcasting_board_of_governors" occur="3" src="named_federal_agencies">Broadcasting Board of Governors</span> renamed United States Agency for Global Media pursuant to <a href="/uscode/text/22/6204#a_21">section 6204(a)(21) of this title</a>. The renaming was effectuated by notice to congressional appropriations committees dated <span class="date" date="2018-05-24">May 24, 2018</span>, and became effective <span class="date" date="2018-08-22">Aug. 22, 2018</span>.</p>
</div>
<div class="note" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment"><span class="heading centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 2012 Amendment</span>
<p>Amendment by <a href="/rio/citation/Pub._L._112-166">Pub. L. 112–166</a> effective 60 days after <span class="date" date="2012-08-10">Aug. 10, 2012</span>, and applicable to appointments made on and after that effective date, including any nomination pending in the <span link="https://liicornell.org/liifedent/cong_senate" occur="25" src="named_federal_agencies">Senate</span> on that date, see <a href="/rio/citation/Pub._L._112-166">section 6(a) of Pub. L. 112–166</a>, set out as a note under <a href="/uscode/text/6/113">section 113 of Title 6</a>, Domestic Security.</p>
